{"type":"message","id":"731f4ba8","parentId":"c0a4cad4","timestamp":"2026-02-28T02:12:14.497Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"chatcmpl-tool-9e80458a589991ae","toolName":"web_search","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Title: The Egyptian Exchange - Listing - All Listed Securities - Stocks\nURL: https://www.egx.com.eg/en/listedstocks.aspx\nText: This question is for testing whether you are a human visitor and to prevent automated spam submission.\nAudio is not supported in your browser.[] \n**What code is in the image?**\nsubmit\nYour support ID is: 10680795860807795709.\n\nTitle: Centamin Egypt - Pharaoh Gold Mines NL\nAuthor: \nURL: https://egypt-business.com/company/details/Centamin-Egypt---Pharaoh-Gold-Mines-NL\nText: Centamin Egypt - Pharaoh Gold Mines NL\n[![Logo]] \n**\n[REGISTER] |[LOGIN] [![Marketing-Börse PLUS - Fachbeiträge zu Marketing und Digitalisierung]] \n**\n[![Logo]] \n[![Marketing-Börse PLUS - Fachbeiträge zu Marketing und Digitalisierung]] \n![print logo] \n# Centamin Egypt - Pharaoh Gold Mines NL\n![Centamin Egypt - Pharaoh Gold Mines NL] \n## **Are a rapidly growing gold producer with their flagship project, the Sukari Gold Mine, located in the Eastern Desert of Egypt.**\n* [Mining] \n| Alexandria, Egypt\n[Energy] \n* [![ASCOM]] \n[ASCOM] EG\n* [![Misr Phosphate]] \n[Misr Phosphate] Cairo EG\n* [![Nubian Mining Company]] \n[Nubian Mining Company] Cairo EG\n000004348200001774010000177403\nHomeAboutProductsPostsJobs\n### News:\n* [Centamin plc Completion of Redomicile and Commencement of Trading] \n* [Citi cuts target price for Centamin Egypt amid political unrest] \n* [Return of Street Fighting in Cairo Has Centamin Egypt Falling Again; Shares Now 24% Lower Over Past] \n[more ...] \n### Focus\n* **[Energy] **-[Mining] \n361 El-Horreya Road, Sedi Gaber\nAlexandria\nEgypt\nTelephone: +20 3 5411259\nTelefax: +20 3 5226350\n361 El-Horreya Road, Sedi Gaber\nAlexandria\nEgypt\nTelephone: +20 3 5411259\nTelefax: +20 3 5226350\n[https://www.centamin.com/] \nno contents for products ...\nno posts ...\nno contents for jobs ...\n[Add company] \n[Energy news] \n## [Egypt, Sudan worry about water as Ethiopia&#039;s mega dam opens] \nEthiopia has high hopes for its Grand Ethiopian Renaissance Dam, which is expected to double the nation&#039;s electricity capacity.\n## [Badawi Outlines Egypt’s Strategy to Attract Investment, Secure Local Needs at Gastech 2025] \nA comprehensive package of measures, including investment incentives and the settlement of foreign partners’ receivables is also essential.\n## [BP signs preliminary deal with Egypt&#039;s EGAS to drill five Mediterranea\n\nTitle: Centamin Egypt/Pharaoh Gold Mines, Adexen.com\nAuthor: Adexen\nURL: https://www.adexen.com/company/211183\nText: Centamin Egypt/Pharaoh Gold Mines, Adexen.com\n![Loading..] \n[![Adexen]] [Logout] \n[![Centamin Egypt/Pharaoh Gold Mines]] ### [Centamin Egypt/Pharaoh Gold Mines] \n#### Mining & Metals\n[**Website] \n201-500 employees\n* [Home] \n* [Jobs] \n* [Followers] \n* [Notifications] \n* [reviews] \n### Admin Center\n#### Drive engagement\nPosting daily company updates is the most effective way to start a conversation, and create word of mouth for your business. View tips\n![] \ntest imagetest image\n[**] \n**Upload an Image\nShare With: PublicShare With: ConnectionsShare\nYear found\n2009\n##### HeadquartersAlexandria, Egypt\nCentamin plc is a mineral exploration, development and mining company dual listed on the London and Toronto Stock Exchanges.\nCentamin's principal asset, the Sukari Gold Mine, began production in 2009 and is the first large scale modern gold mine in Egypt. Base case production is c. 500,000 ounces per annum, with the potential to exceed this level as optimisation of the mining and processing operations continues.\nOur solid financial position, strong cash flows and development and operating experience provides us with a significant advantage in acquiring and developing other gold projects.\nOur most advanced exploration projects are located in highly prospective regions within the investor-friendly jurisdictions of Burkina Faso and Cote d'Ivoire.\n## Similar Companies[View All**] \n1. ![Frontier Oil Ltd] \n[Frontier Oil Ltd] \nEnergy / Oil & Gas\n201-500 employees\nLagos, Nigeria\n2. ![Cakasa (Nigeria) Company Limited] \n[Cakasa (Nigeria) Company Limited] \nEnergy / Oil & Gas\n201-500 employees\nLagos, Nigeria\n3. ![Eroton Exploration and Production Company Limited] \n[Eroton Exploration and Production Company Limited] \nEnergy / Oil & Gas\n201-500 employees\nLagos, Nigeria\n4. ![Neconde Energy Limited] \n[Neconde Energy Limited] \nEnergy / Oil & Gas\n201-500 employees\nLagos, Nig\n\nTitle: 10 Egyptian stocks outperform gold, real estate, and savings certificates in Q2 2025 - Dailynewsegypt\nAuthor: Daily News Egypt\nURL: https://www.dailynewsegypt.com/2025/07/06/10-egyptian-stocks-outperform-gold-real-estate-and-savings-certificates-in-q2-2025/\nText: 10 Egyptian stocks outperform gold, real estate, and savings certificates in Q2 2025 - Dailynewsegypt\n\nSHARE\n\nTen stocks listed on the Egyptian Exchange (EGX) posted exceptional gains during the second quarter of 2025, with share prices soaring by more than 70%—significantly outperforming traditional investment options such as gold, real estate, and bank savings certificates. The rally was fuelled by a combination of strong financial results and speculative trading, particularly in small- and mid-cap stocks.\n\nAmong the top gainers, U Consumer Finance recorded a staggering increase of 1,019.69%, closing the quarter at EGP 8.700, marking the most dramatic surge on the market. ODIN Investments in Egyptian Equities – Kasb followed with a 443% rise to EGP 5.430. Egypt Fertilizers (EGYFERT) jumped 111.48% to close at EGP 216.510, while Upper Egypt Flour Mills advanced 108.53% to EGP 551.700. Misr Cement Qena also delivered strong gains, rising 102.11% to reach EGP 52.730.\n\nMisr Beni Suef Cement saw its share price climb by 92.93%, ending the quarter at EGP 144.700. General Silos & Storage (GSSC) appreciated by 86.65% to EGP 313.860, and Beltone Holding gained 77.99%, closing at EGP 3.720. Suez Canal Technology Settling rose 74.38% to EGP 154.400, while Cairo National Company for Investment and Securities increased 73.76% to EGP 52.040. B Investments Holding completed the list with a 72.04% rise, reaching EGP 40.00 per share.\n\nDespite the remarkable performance of these individual stocks, broader market indices posted more modest gains. The benchmark EGX30, which tracks the performance of the 30 most liquid companies on the exchange, rose by 2.6% to close the quarter at 32,857.62 points. The EGX70 Equal W\n\nTitle: EGX 100 EWI Companies Stock List - Investing.com\nURL: https://www.investing.com/indices/egx-100-ewi-components\nText: EGX 100 EWI Companies Stock List - Investing.com\n\n# EGX 100 EWI (EGX100EWI)\n\nEgypt\n\nCurrency in EGP\n\nAdd to Watchlist\n\nDelayed Data·04:23:30\n\n## EGX 100 EWI Companies\n\nPricePerformanceTechnicalFundamental\n\nName\n\nLast\n\nHigh\n\nLow\n\nChg. %\n\nVol.\n\nUpside\n\nTime\n\n#### Arab Cotton Ginning\n\n#### Qalaa Holdings\n\n#### Commercial Int Bank\n\n#### Egyptian Tourism Resorts\n\n#### Valmore Holding\n\n#### Electro Cable\n\n#### El Kahera Housing\n\n#### Telecom Egypt\n\n#### EFG Hermes Holdings\n\n#### Maridive & oil Svcs\n\n#### Egyptian Media Production City\n\n#### SODIC\n\n#### Palm Hills Develop\n\n#### Aspire Capital Holding for Financial Investments\n\n#### Sidi Kerir\n\n#### South Valley Cement\n\n#### El Sewedy Electric\n\n#### T M G Holding\n\n#### El Saeed Contracting & RE Inv\n\n#### ODIN Investments SAE\n\n#### ASEC Co for Mining\n\n#### GB AUTO\n\n#### Cairo Oils & Soap\n\n#### Canal Shipping Agencies\n\n#### Al Ezz\n\n#### Egyptians Housing Develop\n\n#### El Shams\n\n#### Industrial Engineering\n\n#### Egyptian Transport & Commercial Services\n\n#### Giza General Contracting\n\n#### Housing&Develop Bank\n\n#### Misr El Gadida for Housing Dev\n\n#### Int Agricultural Products\n\n#### Ismailia Misr Poultry\n\n#### El Nasr Clothing & Textiles\n\n#### Lecico Egypt\n\n#### Mena Touristic&RE\n\n#### Madinet Nasr for Housing and Development\n\n#### Mansourah Poultry\n\n#### Oriental Weavers\n\n#### Cairo Poultry\n\n#### Ceramic&Porcelain\n\n#### Raya Holding\n\n#### Delta Sugar\n\n#### United Housing&Develop\n\n#### Zahraa Maadi\n\n#### Abu Qir Fertilizers and Chemical Industries\n\n#### Misr Cement\n\n#### Alexandria Mineral Oils\n\n#### Credit Agricole Egypt\n\n#### Eastern Tobacco\n\n#### Egypt Gas\n\n#### EIPICO\n\n#### Kima\n\n#### Sinai Cement\n\n#### EDBE\n\n#### ARAB DAIRY\n\n#### Arabia Invest\n\n#### Alexandria Containers&goods\n\n#### Amer Group Holding\n\n#### Arab Moltaka Invest\n\n#### Misr National Steel\n\n#### Beltone Financial Hld\n\n#### Ceramica Rem\n\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1772244734489}}
